--------------- Original Message ---------------
From: Netwrix Support [techsupport@netwrix.com]
Sent: 3/6/2025 7:09 PM
To: hworrall@grosscollins.com
Subject: RE: Netwrix Support Ticket #437927 - - Needs help deleting things [ ref:!00D70091pB.!500Qk0McuRC:ref ]

Hi Heather,

Thank you! We have cleared some pace in the backend. You should be now at around 52% disk space occupied from 80%. Please allow around 15 minutes for changes to replicare on the EPP server UI end.

Please be aware that I saw that the periodic database backups were occupying a lot of space, and as these are done every 3 or so days the issue may come back in a few weeks/months.

In order to prevent this please try:
- using the Audit Log Backup functionality -> it will archive the logs and remove them from the EPP server(you can apply this to old logs).
- this functionality can be enabled from System Maintenance -> Audit Log Backup

Please let me know if we can close this ticket.

Best Regards,
Flaviu Moldovan | Technical Support Engineer
Endpoint Protector by CoSoSys, now part of Netwrix
DLP | Device Control | Content Aware Protection | eDiscovery | Enforced Encryption
www.endpointprotector.com
